The Herald Senior Reporter ZANU PF will have its first Politburo meeting of the year tomorrow, the party’s Secretary for Information and Publicity, Cde Christopher Mutsvangwa, said yesterday. In a statement, Cde Mutsvangwa said: “The Secretary for Administration Cde Dr O.M. Mpofu wishes to advise all members that there shall be an ordinary session of the Politburo to be held on Wednesday 1 March 2023 at the home of the people’s revolution, Zanu PF headquarters commencing 10 00 hours.” All members should be seated by 0945 hours.